A Location must have either a spatial relation to another location (e.g. "contained in"), a geographical coordinate representing its centre, or a pair of geographical coordintes representing it's outer boundaries (northwest/southeast)


An instance of Location can have a PopularName and isLocatedAt a geographical point.

E.g. Defining Stockholm as a Location:
LocationUUID#1 isA Location
LocationUUID#1 hasPopularName "Stockholm"
LocationUUID#1 isLocatedAt (59.333683,18.068579,0)
LocationUUID#1 isLocatedIn LocationUUID#2

Cognitive clustering of time-related properties that can apply to time-indexed objects (i.e., events of various sorts).

Certain time properties are given using xsd:DateTime, i.e., ISO8601 (see below), whereas others are given as ints or floats, depending on use case.

Time format ISO8601:

Complete date, hour, minutes, seconds, and decimal fraction of second

      YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD (eg 1997-07-16T19:20:30.45+01:00)

Where:
     YYYY = 4 numbers for year.
     MM = 2 numbers for month (01=January, etc.)
     DD = 2 numbers for day of month (01 till 31)
     hh = 2 numbers for hour (00 till 23) (am/pm not allowed)
     mm = 2 numbers for minutes (00 till 59)
     ss = 2 numbers for second (00 till 59)
     s = 1 or more numbers represent a decimal fraction of second

TZD  = time zone designator (Z or +hh:mm or -hh:mm)
Time is expressed in UTC (Coordinated Universal Time), with designated UTC  ("Z") for GMT.

A generic clustering of meronomy (parthood) relations, allowing for the traversal of the parthood taxonomy of a real estate. Note that this is a transitive property.

Indicates which building a given building component is part of. Note that the parthood hierarchy is transitive, so every building component does not necessarily need to be invidiually connected to a building or a real estate; this can be inferred through the more generic isPartOf property.
Indicates that a building structure or a piece of land belongs to / is part of a given real estate.

For example an airtreatment device (Device) that serves several rooms (BuildingStructureComponent) or a full building (BuildingStructure). Can also be a Device (e.g. airtreatment device) serving another Device (e.g. air diffuser).
